# Environment Variables for MEDEVAC Application
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values

# Azure SQL Database Configuration
AZURE_SQL_SERVER=your-server-name.database.windows.net
AZURE_SQL_USER=your-username
AZURE_SQL_PASSWORD=your-password
AZURE_SQL_DATABASE=your-database-name

# Application Configuration
NODE_ENV=development
PORT=3001

# Security (generate random strings for production)
SESSION_SECRET=your-session-secret-key
JWT_SECRET=your-jwt-secret-key

# Instructions:
# 1. Create an Azure SQL Database:
#    - Go to Azure Portal (portal.azure.com)
#    - Create a new SQL Database
#    - Note the server name, database name, and login credentials
#
# 2. Configure firewall:
#    - In Azure SQL Database settings, go to "Set server firewall"
#    - Add your IP address to allow connections
#    - For development, you can temporarily allow all IPs (0.0.0.0 - 255.255.255.255)
#    - For production, restrict to specific IPs only
#
# 3. Fill in the values above:
#    - AZURE_SQL_SERVER: Your server name (e.g., myserver.database.windows.net)
#    - AZURE_SQL_USER: Admin username you created
#    - AZURE_SQL_PASSWORD: Admin password you created
#    - AZURE_SQL_DATABASE: Your database name
#
# 4. Generate secure secrets:
#    - SESSION_SECRET: Random string for session encryption
#    - JWT_SECRET: Random string for JWT token signing
#
# 5. Run the setup script:
#    node scripts/setup-azure-db.js